statement:
Consider two coplanar circles of radii \( R \) and \( r \) (\( R > r \)) with the same center. Let \( P \) be a fixed point on the smaller circle and \( B \) a variable point on the larger circle. The line \( BP \) meets the larger circle again at \( C \). The perpendicular \( \ell \) to \( BP \) at \( P \) meets the smaller circle again at \( A \). (If \( \ell \) is tangent to the circle at \( P \) then \( A = P \).)
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(i)] Find the set of values of \( BC^2 + CA^2 + AB^2 \).
\item[(ii)] Find the locus of the midpoint of \( BC \).
\end{enumerate}
